headline: American Airstrikes Stir Anger From the Iraqis
abstract: After months of turmoil in Iraq, U.S. airstrikes against a pro-Iranian militia drew a backlash.
lead_paragraph: For months, furious protests have battered Iraq, driven by frustration at a dysfunctional economy, corruption and the pervasive influence of a foreign power: Iran.
keywords: United States Defense and Military Forces
